Tolerate an unset API key on a keyless boot.

NanoBanana::__construct guards on the *config* value (`api_key`), which on the
AIncient distribution is the Key ENTITY id (`nanobanana_default_key`) shipped in
config/sync — so it is always truthy. On a fresh, keyless install the entity's
backing Drupal State value is unset, so KeyInterface::getKeyValue() returns NULL,
and assigning NULL to the typed `string $apiKey` property throws a TypeError at
service construction. That takes down any request that merely enumerates the
image provider (the onboarding wizard on first run, the Media studio) — e.g. the
whole /aincient console 500s until an operator manually seeds the State key.

Coalesce a missing key to '' so the client constructs cleanly and simply stays
unconfigured until onboarding stores a real key (the sole key path on AIncient).

--- a/src/NanoBanana.php
+++ b/src/NanoBanana.php
@@ -46,7 +46,7 @@ class NanoBanana {
     $this->client = $client;
     $key = $configFactory->get(NanoBananaConfigForm::CONFIG_NAME)->get('api_key') ?? '';
     if ($key) {
-      $this->apiKey = $keyRepository->getKey($key)->getKeyValue();
+      $this->apiKey = $keyRepository->getKey($key)?->getKeyValue() ?? '';
     }
   }

